column5: Major rain today at camp.. unearthed these?    I think they are wood stove cranks that stirred up the coals in the stove.. anybody else got any ideas?
Think so too ( spring handle )...we found some very similar by Sarge a few years back .
It just weird.. cause there were three different ones .. all together.
HMMM.. so once upon a time someone else drank whiskey in that exact same spot...

I see the size of your thumb now .. I sent the picture to my brother , he recalls my Dad having some ,  my other brother apparently has them ( says the wood is burned off ) has no clue what they are .
Look like some kind of drill bit or rasp to me .. a prospectors tool. ... TJ ?
Yep, wood stove ash crank thing.
I would say they are the turn outs from a coal stove, not wood. Someone probably used the stove for wood, and dumped those right where you found them.  S
Yes, we had those in our coal furnace in the 50's. The 3 of them mesh together.  Edit to add: Here's a link I found. http://www.woodmanspartsplus.com/4865/Stove-Grates-Triplex.html
Is that 1850's or 1950's Roy?   Love yaa   Art
That was the 1950's Arthur. 1850's would have been J's.  Geez I'm in trouble now.....
